### Problem05

```java
public class StackCheck
{
    public static boolean check (int [] a)
    {
        Stack <Integer> stack =  new Stack<>();
        for (int i : a )
        {
            if (stack.size()==0){stack.push(i);continue;}
            if (__0__){stack.pop(); continue;}
            stack.push(i);
        }
        return __1__;
    }
}
```

Please complete the method check() above so that it can tell if the number of 0 and 1 in the int[]a is the same.

Example_1:

int[]a={0,1,1}
check(a)=false

Example_2

int[]a={0,1,1,0}
check(a)=true

